    <br/>
    <h3>Get Musician by Name</h3>
    <p>
       You can get details of the artist by his first name and last name. For that you can use <strong>first_name</strong> and <strong>last_name</strong>
        tags available with the API. It is not required to provide both. You can get entries from either <strong>first_name</strong> or <strong>last_name</strong>.
        But there are chances that there may be same first name or last name of singer.
    </p>
    <strong class="alert-info">API CALL WITH FIRST NAME</strong>
    <br/>
    <em>api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?first_name={first name or band name}</em>
    <br/>
    <strong class="text-info">PARAMETERS</strong>
    <br/>
    <em>first_name</em>
    <p>Note: this parameter is not case sensative. It is also used to get the bands like maroon 5, coldplay and many more who are not having last names.</p>
    <strong class="text-info">EXAMPLES</strong>
    <br />
    <a href="http://api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?first_name=david">api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?first_name=david</a><br/>
    <a href="http://api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?first_name=coldplay">api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?first_name=coldplay</a><br/>
    <a href="http://api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?first_name=maroon%205">api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?first_name=maroon 5</a>
    <br/>
    <br/>
    <strong class="alert-info">API CALL WITH LAST NAME</strong>
    <br />
    <em>api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?last_name={last name}</em>
    <br />
    <strong class="text-info">PARAMETERS</strong>
    <br />
    <em>last_name</em>
    <p>Note: this parameter is not case sensative. If you are searching for band or singer without last name, leave this parameter or pass the value null</p>
    <strong class="text-info">EXAMPLES</strong>
    <br />
    <a href="http://api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?last_name=minaj">api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?last_name=minaj</a><br />
    <a href="http://api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?last_name=garrix">api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?last_name=garrix</a><br />
    <a href="http://api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?last_name=null">api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?last_name=null</a>
    <br />
    <br />
    <strong class="alert-info">API CALL WITH FULL NAME</strong>
    <br />
    <em>api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?first_name={first name}&last_name={last name}</em>
    <br />
    <strong class="text-info">PARAMETERS</strong>
    <br />
    <em>first_name</em>
    <br/>
    <em>last_name</em>
    <p>Note: Both parameters are not case sensative. They can be used together to get the artist who is having first & last name. If using both but not having last name of artist, put null as value</p>
    <strong class="text-info">EXAMPLES</strong>
    <br />
    <a href="http://api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?first_name=nicki&last_name=minaj">api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?first_name=nicki&last_name=minaj</a><br />
    <a href="http://api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?first_name=martin&last_name=garrix">api-music.azurewebsites.net/api/artists?first_name=martin&last_name=garrix</a><br />
